                <head>Inhabitants of Sheffield</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Sheffield</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1865-05-01">May 1, 1865</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolution passed at a meeting held by the inhabitants of the
                        borough of Sheffield, England</hi>.</p>
                <p>At a meeting of the inhabitants of the borough of Sheffield, in the county of
                    York, England, held on Monday, May 1, 1865, Thomas Jessop, esq., in the chair,
                    it was</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Unanimously resolved</hi>, That this meeting condemns in the
                    strongest possible sense the dastardly and cruel murder of President Lincoln, in
                    the hour of his clemency, and records its utmost abhorrence of the atrocious
                    miscreants who planned and the wretches who perpetrated the hideous, detestable
                    and unparalleled crime; and that the Right Honorable Earl Russell be requested
                    to transmit this resolution, in the manner most befitting the occasion, to the
                    government and citizens of the United States, assuring them of the profound and
                    sincere regret of the inhabitants of Sheffield at the bereavement, and their,
                    firm hope <pb facs="0410" n="338" xml:id="pg_338"/> that, as in the past, so
                    with this sad occurrence, the United States will show by their calmness, wisdom,
                    and energy, that though of appalling magnitude, their loss is not
                    irretrievable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>THOMAS JESSOP,</signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mayor and Chairman</hi>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
